sec.p:
The subfamily ptereleotrinae previously contained five genera and 48 species, with most species found in the Indo-Pacific regions (
Hoese et al ., 2006 ). Three additional species have been described since then. The genera have been partly revised in a series of publications: Aioliops Rennis & Hoese (Rennis & Hoese, 1987 )
, Nemateleotris Fowler (
Randall & Allen, 1973 )
, Oxymetopon Bleeker (
Klausewitz & Conde, 1981 )
, Parioglossus Regan
(
Rennis & Hoese, 1985 ;
Dingerkus & Séret, 1992 ;
Keith et al ., 2004 ;
McDowall, 2001 ; Susuki &
Senou, 1994 ;
Williams & Lecchini, 2004 ;
Zhong, 1994 ); Ptereleotris Gill
(
Randall & Hoese, 1985 ;
Randall & Susuki, 2008 ;
Bussing, 2001 ;
Gasparini et al ., 2001 ).
